<!-- About Content -->
<section class="about-story-section container">
  <div class="story-grid">
    <div class="story-text">
      <h2>Crafting Bold Flavors Since 2020</h2>
      <p>
        Spicery Co. was founded in Seattle, Washington, by a small group of chefs and culinary enthusiasts who were frustrated by the stale, dusty spice offerings in traditional grocery stores. We realized that while American home cooks were investing in premium meats, organic vegetables, and high-end cookware, they were seasoning their meals with ingredients that had sat in warehouses for years, losing their essential oils and flavors.
      </p>
      <p>
        We set out to change that by building direct relationships with independent farmers and agricultural cooperatives around the globe. From the volcanic soils of Sumatra for our Korintje Cinnamon, to family farms in Extremadura, Spain for our Smoked Paprika, we select only the highest grade crops.
      </p>
      
      <blockquote>
        "The difference between a good dish and an unforgettable culinary memory lies in the oils of the spice."
      </blockquote>
      
      <h3>Our Triple Promise</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Strict Batch Rotation:</strong> We grind our whole spices in small batches weekly and pack them immediately, guaranteeing unparalleled potency.</li>
        <li><strong>Zero Fillers:</strong> Our spices are 100% pure. We never add flow agents, silica, artificial colors, or cheap starch extenders.</li>
        <li><strong>Ethical Partnerships:</strong> By cutting out mid-tier distributors, we pay our growers premium rates that support sustainable regional farming.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    
    <div class="story-imagery">
      <div class="image-wrapper-bordered">
        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1599940824399-b87987ceb72a?q=80&w=600&auto=format&fit=crop" alt="Grinding raw spices in mortar">
      </div>
      <div class="story-stat-badge">
        <span class="stat-number">100%</span>
        <span class="stat-desc">Pure & Fresh Ground</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

